text:
Set in the 1990s, Captain Marvel follows Danvers, an Air Force officer, as she becomes one of the universe's most powerful heroes after earth gets involved in a galactic war between alien. Brie Larson stars in the title role alongside Samuel L Jackson, Ben Mendelsohn and Jude Law.
The new trailer for 'Captain Marvel' is out and it looks like an action-packed ride! After watching it, we can't help but wonder - what are Carol Danvers' powers? Well, let's dive into them!
1. Superhuman Strength: As seen in the trailer, Carol can lift and toss around heavy objects with ease. She possesses incredible strength that makes her almost unbeatable in hand-to-hand combat.
2. Speed and Agility: Danvers can move at incredible velocities, making her capable of dodging attacks and traversing vast distances in a short span.
3. Durability: With her human-Kree hybrid physiology, Carol has enhanced resilience to injury. She can withstand extreme temperatures, explosions, and other forms of damage that would be lethal to humans.
4. Energy Projection: As seen in the trailer, Carol can project powerful blasts of energy from her hands. This ability allows her to blast through solid objects or incapacitate enemies.
5. Flight: One of her most iconic abilities, Captain Marvel can defy gravity and soar through space. This power enables her to respond quickly to threats across the galaxy.
6. Regeneration: Carol has accelerated healing capabilities, allowing her to recover rapidly from injuries that would be debilitating for humans.
